The paper discusses kinodynamic motion planning, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed approach involves using machine learning frameworks (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.LG) to infer local maneuvers for the robotic system. The paper also mentions the use of obstacle and heuristic information, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY) and computer vision (cs.CV), respectively.
